# React Component Guidelines

## Component Structure
- Use functional components with hooks
- Follow the single responsibility principle
- Keep components focused on specific medical workflows
- Use proper TypeScript interfaces for props

## File Organization
- One component per file
- Co-locate related components in feature directories
- Use index files for clean exports
- Follow the pattern: `ComponentName.tsx`

## Component Naming
- Use PascalCase for component names
- Use descriptive names that reflect medical functionality
- Prefix with domain when needed (e.g., `MTFDetection`, `PatientAssessment`)

## Props and State
- Define clear prop interfaces
- Use proper default values
- Implement proper state management patterns
- Use React Query for server state

## Medical UI Components
- Follow healthcare design guidelines from [design_guidelines.md](mdc:design_guidelines.md)
- Use Radix UI components as base
- Implement proper accessibility for medical interfaces
- Use medical-appropriate color schemes and typography

